": "324017"}, {"#name": "pixel-height", "_": "778"}, {"#name": "pixel-width", "_": "1333"}, {"#name": "attachment-type", "_": "IMAGE-HIGH-RES"}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"id": "abs0001", "class": "author-highlights", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "cesectitle0001"}, "_": "Highlights"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "abss0001", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "spara012", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "list", "$": {"id": "celist0001"}, "$$": [{"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "celistitem0001"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "para0005", "view": "all"}, "_": "A technique to remotely reconfigure the entire FPGA in distributed sensor nodes."}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "celistitem0002"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "para0006", "view": "all"}, "_": "Uses small amount of reconfiguration logic, but no microcontroller or softcore processor."}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "celistitem0003"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "para0007", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "__text__", "_": "Fully wireless upload of new configuration "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "bitstream"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " to sensor node's flash memory."}]}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "celistitem0004"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "para0008", "view": "all"}, "_": "Remote reconfiguration and wireless upload operations do not drastically increase the sensor node's power consumption."}]}]}]}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"id": "abs0002", "view": "all", "class": "author"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "cesectitle0002"}, "_": "Abstract"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "abss0002", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "spara013", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "__text__", "_": "Recently, sensor nodes in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) have been using Field Programmable Gate Arrays (FPGA) for high-speed, low-power processing and reconfigurability. Reconfigurability enables adaptation of functionality and performance to changing requirements. This paper presents an efficient architecture for full remote reconfiguration of FPGA-based wireless sensors. The novelty of the work includes the ability to wirelessly upload new configuration "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "bitstreams"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " to remote sensor nodes using a protocol developed to provide full remote access to the flash memory of the sensor nodes. Results show that the FPGA can be remotely reconfigured in 1.35\u00a0s using a "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "bitstream"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " stored in the flash memory. The proposed scheme uses negligible amount of FPGA logic and does not require a dedicated microcontroller or softcore processor. It can help develop truly flexible IoT, where the FPGAs on thousands of sensor nodes can be reprogrammed or new configuration "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "bitstreams"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " uploaded without requiring physical access to the nodes."}]}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"id": "abs0003", "class": "graphical", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "cesectitle0003"}, "_": "Graphical abstract"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "abss0003", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "spara014", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "display", "$$": [{"#name": "figure", "$": {"id": "fig0009"}, "$$": [{"#name": "alt-text", "$": {"id": "alttx001", "role": "short"}, "_": "Image, graphical abstract"}, {"#name": "link", "$": {"xmlns:xlink": true, "id": "celink0009", "locator": "ga1", "type": "simple", "role": "http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4", "href": "pii:S0045790622002154/ga1"}}]}]}]}]}]}]}}